        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-08-11 17:42:20.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nYeah wonder if that is a checkstyle issue?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "059358cc7084e386c955081eff95df6ad138488a",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 477,
          "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
          "username": "jhh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-08-11 17:50:02.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI'm wondering if we could disable checkstyle localy in just our repos until we are ready to tackle these warningd.   There may be many hundreds of complaints, probably thousands across all of the policy repos, and it will certainly makes challenging to look for valuable information in the log files that I check sometimes.  It may make sense for new repos, to start clean, but for an already existing base, it obscures other much more valuable information from the build logs.   What's your take?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "8c8b31720002030525f20d28ae9fa3178321826f",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 57,
          "name": "Pamela Dragosh",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "pd1248@att.com",
          "username": "pdragosh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-08-11 18:25:48.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2\n\nI don't think its hurting anything right now. Let's not bother for now - I would rather folks spent cycles removing the warnings vs removing the generation of the warnings.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
